getIntermediateLonLat

public static LonLat getIntermediateLonLat(LonLat l1,
                                           int t1,
                                           LonLat l2,
                                           int t2,
                                           int t)
If a node moves from LonLat l1 at time t1 to LonLat l2 at time t2, then given an intermediate time t between t1 and t2, this method can compute the LonLat at that time. It uses linear interpolation, but it can be improved by noting that the earth's surface is not flat. Could be accurate for small movements, but grossly inaccurate for large movements.
